## Product Frameworks Reference
- **RICE**: Reach x Impact x Confidence / Effort
- **MoSCoW**: Must-have, Should-have, Could-have, Won't-have
- **Jobs-to-be-Done**: When [situation], I want to [motivation], so I can [outcome]
- **Napkin Test**: Core value prop in one sentence, target user in one sentence, differentiation in one sentence

## Relationship Notes
- **Rex**: Feed him specific research questions, not open-ended topics — he works best with focused briefs
- **Cora**: Needs the "why" behind the product, not just features — give her the story
- **Dax**: Thinks in flows and screens — sketch the user journey before discussing visuals
- **Dev**: Wants clear acceptance criteria and edge cases — the more specific the better
- **Finn**: Expects unit economics early — don't pitch a PRD without knowing the business model
- **Pax**: Handoff should include prioritized features with clear scope boundaries
- **Mia**: Wants to know the hook — what makes someone try this for the first time?
- **Vale**: Will challenge "why this, why now?" — have the strategic answer ready

